TopicTitle: Folding Plane .craft files **FIXED for realz!** Updated 6/2/2012

Articles.Content:
First of you have to have the Damned Robotics Version 1.1 and Anatid Robotics / MuMech - MechJeb - Autopilot - v1.8.4

Apparently I used a couple of parts from C7 Aerospace Division - Part 3 and the C7 Flight Pack too. Sorry for not linking this needed stuff earlier.

Floodlights are here: Omega Aerospace

NP*stuff* parts from: NovaPunch Remix Pack

**UPDATED** Next you need a bunch of hinges that I tweaked based off of Damnyoujapan\'s and r4m0n\'s work in the above add-on, extra thanks to them for making these awesome toys or us to play with! The modified hinges are the attachment 'ModifiedDRstuff.zip' . Just extract them into your parts folder.

The 'dropship 1.craft' attachment is the drop ship from this video

The 'Folder 2.craft' attachment is the folding fighter

The 'Folder 3.craft' attachment is the Glider

The 'folder 4.craft' attachment is the vertical folder

The 'Cargo Plane 1.craft' attachment is The Flying Dumpster, 1/2 open the bay doors, 9/0 fold and unfold the drop vehicle. The inner folding plane starts folded, so DO NOT unfold before starting.

The 'folder6' attachment is my first try with the new door hinges.

The 'Bomber.craft' attachment was my first try with an internal bay. I actually don\'t remember what I used to retract the landing struts.. probably 5/6 or 7/8

VTOL Folder! 1/2 for engine angle control, 5/6 for landing gear armature, 9/0 to old/unfold

The Flying Pancake

Rhino Cargo Plane w/ Folding Glider (requires DRdoorhinge90 & NP_Fairings_3m_Wall_Solid)

The SPC (requires Vlad\'s Airbrakes and Spider Tech Engines as well as the modified DamnedRobotics hinges from the attachments.. almost forgot Modular Missiles from JellyCubes hopefully no more that I have forgotten)

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KC0NDVk4X3g

Ultra RCS attachment is a blatant cheat part that I use for testing and balancing, but I may have left it on a craft or 2.

All of these start unfolded for the most part. Use \'0\' and \'9\' to fold or unfold, and make sure to unfold them all the way before you start.
